  "prompt": "What are some best songs to listen to?",
  "response": "The best songs can vary greatly depending on personal taste and the mood you're in, but here\u2019s a diverse selection across different genres and eras that many people enjoy:\n\n### Pop\n1. **\"Blinding Lights\" by The Weeknd**\n2. **\"Levitating\" by Dua Lipa**\n3. **\"Shake It Off\" by Taylor Swift**\n\n### Rock\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen**\n2. **\"Hotel California\" by Eagles**\n3. **\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" by Nirvana**\n\n### Hip-Hop/Rap\n1. **\"Sicko Mode\" by Travis Scott**\n2. **\"Alright\" by Kendrick Lamar**\n3. **\"Lose Yourself\" by Eminem**\n\n### R&B/Soul\n1. **\"Redbone\" by Childish Gambino**\n2. **\"Ain't No Sunshine\" by Bill Withers**\n3. **\"Blame It on the Juice\" by Lizzo**\n\n### Indie/Alternative\n1. **\"Take Me Out\" by Franz Ferdinand**\n2. **\"Dog Days Are Over\" by Florence + The Machine**\n3. **\"Electric Feel\" by MGMT**\n\n### Classic Hits\n1. **\"Imagine\" by John Lennon**\n2. **\"Superstition\" by Stevie Wonder**\n3. **\"What's Going On\" by Marvin Gaye**\n\n### Electronic/Dance\n1. **\"Titanium\" by David Guetta feat. Sia**\n2. **\"Wake Me Up\" by Avicii**\n3. **\"Strobe\" by Deadmau5**\n\n### Country\n1. **\"Jolene\" by Dolly Parton**\n2. **\"Before He Cheats\" by Carrie Underwood**\n3. **\"Wagon Wheel\" by Old Crow Medicine Show**\n\n### Chill/Acoustic\n1. **\"Budapest\" by George Ezra**\n2. **\"Banana Pancakes\" by Jack Johnson**\n3. **\"Skinny Love\" by Bon Iver**\n\nFeel free to let me know if you're looking for more specific recommendations or songs tailored to a particular mood or event!",
